title: 134: I See Satan Fall Like Lightning
dc:creator: A.J. Hanenburg
description: Whenever Graeme likes to say something intelligent, one thing that I apparently love to do is fasten on one small element of his argument and dig my heels in. This week, it's about birds that love each other. The rest of the podcast is a cool thing about psychological readings of scripture.
itunes:author: Oin, Gloin, and Cottontail
itunes:subtitle: Or maybe it was a wren. Hard to tell.
